THIRD-PARTY SOFTWARE DEPENDENCIES

ClawLite uses the following open-source dependencies:

  python-telegram-bot (LGPL-3.0)
  https://github.com/python-telegram-bot/python-telegram-bot
  Used for Telegram Bot API integration.

  tavily-python (MIT)
  https://github.com/tavily-ai/tavily-python
  Used for real-time web search capabilities.

  ollama (MIT)
  https://github.com/ollama/ollama
  Used for local LLM inference.

  groq (Apache 2.0)
  https://github.com/groq/groq-python
  Used as optional cloud LLM fallback.

  sqlalchemy (MIT)
  https://www.sqlalchemy.org/
  Used for local database ORM.

  sentence-transformers (Apache 2.0)
  https://www.sbert.net/
  Used for local embedding generation and semantic memory recall.

  python-dotenv (BSD-3-Clause)
  https://github.com/theskumar/python-dotenv
  Used for environment variable management.

  fastapi (MIT)
  https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/
  Used for internal health check API.

  uvicorn (BSD-3-Clause)
  https://www.uvicorn.org/
  Used as ASGI server.

  pydantic (MIT)
  https://docs.pydantic.dev/
  Used for data validation.

  loguru (MIT)
  https://github.com/Delgan/loguru
  Used for application logging.

  numpy (BSD-3-Clause)
  https://numpy.org/
  Used for vector operations in semantic memory.

NOTE: The authoritative list of dependencies with exact version pins
is maintained in requirements.txt.

